1
00:02:09,657 --> 00:02:12,394
EV conversion really quieted it down,
didn't it?

2
00:02:12,394 --> 00:02:15,730
You held the corners tight,
handling was sharp as ever.

3
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:18,256
Maybe try F1 next, Chairman.

4
00:02:18,256 --> 00:02:22,404
The cell temp is over 35, so output's capped.

5
00:02:22,404 --> 00:02:25,240
Talk to research about swapping it out.

6
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,042
Higher energy density.

7
00:02:27,042 --> 00:02:28,643
Yes, Chairman.

8
00:02:32,414 --> 00:02:35,917
Not one of them I can trust.

9
00:02:39,985 --> 00:02:43,870
The sun rises right on time,

10
00:02:44,626 --> 00:02:49,130
so why can't people
toughen up after a lifetime?

11
00:02:50,365 --> 00:02:51,648
Sang Jae.

12
00:02:51,648 --> 00:02:53,607
Yes, Chairman.

13
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:55,606
Call in the presidents.

14
00:02:55,606 --> 00:02:57,705
Tell them I have something to say.

15
00:03:07,315 --> 00:03:08,859
Let's go.

16
00:04:25,093 --> 00:04:27,058
We watched you for a month,

17
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:28,872
and that grit and drive

18
00:04:28,872 --> 00:04:31,533
are what set you apart.

19
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:32,570
Thank you.

20
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,469
Time for the first division.

21
00:04:34,469 --> 00:04:36,705
Come to Choiseong.

22
00:04:36,705 --> 00:04:38,672
Seriously?

23
00:04:38,672 --> 00:04:40,642
I'm really playing for Choiseong.

24
00:04:40,642 --> 00:04:41,843
Thank you!

25
00:04:41,843 --> 00:04:43,111
Thank you!

26
00:04:43,111 --> 00:04:44,345
Welcome aboard.

27
00:04:44,345 --> 00:04:46,921
[A signing-on fee of 500 million won
shall be paid to the Player]

28
00:04:50,485 --> 00:04:52,148
[The player, Hwang Jun Hyeon]

29
00:04:53,588 --> 00:04:56,330
Hwang Jun Hyeon, a few words?

30
00:04:56,330 --> 00:04:58,092
I'll give it my all.

31
00:04:58,092 --> 00:04:59,761
I'll work my tail off

32
00:04:59,761 --> 00:05:02,630
and take Choiseong FC to the title.

33
00:05:47,705 --> 00:05:50,444
The Chairman is arriving.

34
00:05:51,605 --> 00:05:53,547
Good morning, Chairman.

35
00:05:55,672 --> 00:05:57,718
Good morning, Chairman.

36
00:06:01,155 --> 00:06:03,548
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

37
00:06:07,595 --> 00:06:09,986
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

38
00:06:44,332 --> 00:06:46,525
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

39
00:06:51,039 --> 00:06:52,139
Sit.

40
00:06:52,139 --> 00:06:54,709
- Good morning, Chairman.
- Good morning, Chairman.

41
00:06:55,777 --> 00:06:57,300
[President Kang Jae Seong]

42
00:07:05,121 --> 00:07:08,156
Choiseong Construction, President Park Gi Mok.

43
00:07:08,156 --> 00:07:10,591
Yes, Chairman.

44
00:07:10,591 --> 00:07:13,428
You've got time to drink.

45
00:07:13,428 --> 00:07:15,129
Must be nice.

46
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:17,767
How did you...

47
00:07:17,767 --> 00:07:20,373
A toast to rally the team would've done,

48
00:07:20,373 --> 00:07:22,804
so why are you the one being poured for?

49
00:07:22,804 --> 00:07:24,106
Don't tell me

50
00:07:24,106 --> 00:07:26,774
your pockets came home full too?

51
00:07:26,774 --> 00:07:28,566
Absolutely not, sir!

52
00:07:28,566 --> 00:07:31,412
The drinks were all on me.

53
00:07:34,516 --> 00:07:39,051
Our goal this year was top five, right?

54
00:07:39,051 --> 00:07:40,521
But at this rate,

55
00:07:40,521 --> 00:07:43,725
we'll drop below tenth before long.

56
00:07:43,725 --> 00:07:47,142
Know why I hit the track every dawn?

57
00:07:47,142 --> 00:07:49,130
To torture you?

58
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:51,032
Some grudge against cars?

59
00:07:51,032 --> 00:07:52,966
No.

60
00:07:55,236 --> 00:07:57,814
To keep my edge.

61
00:07:57,814 --> 00:08:00,475
What drove me to build Choiseong,

62
00:08:00,475 --> 00:08:03,912
what helps us, what hurts us,

63
00:08:03,912 --> 00:08:06,114
every second,

64
00:08:07,249 --> 00:08:10,461
I drill it back in.

65
00:08:14,906 --> 00:08:16,957
So I've decided.

66
00:08:17,925 --> 00:08:21,823
It's time I step away and enjoy retirement.

67
00:08:21,823 --> 00:08:25,632
Choiseong should go to quicker feet.

68
00:08:27,369 --> 00:08:29,637
What's making you do this, sir?

69
00:08:29,637 --> 00:08:31,907
I'm not what I used to be.

70
00:08:31,907 --> 00:08:35,109
My speed, my cornering, all dull,

71
00:08:35,109 --> 00:08:37,378
and my memory keeps slipping.

72
00:08:37,378 --> 00:08:41,516
Strategic Planning will run the succession,

73
00:08:41,516 --> 00:08:43,732
so I want everyone fully on board.

74
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:45,653
- Yes, Chairman.
- Yes, Chairman.

75
00:08:46,695 --> 00:08:49,857
Yes, Chairman?

76
00:08:52,006 --> 00:08:55,072
Back then, when a king named his heir,

77
00:08:55,072 --> 00:08:58,165
every subject begged him to stay,

78
00:08:58,953 --> 00:09:01,714
but you all must have been counting the days

79
00:09:01,714 --> 00:09:04,104
for me to clear out.

80
00:09:06,441 --> 00:09:09,836
Not one of you pushed back.

81
00:09:09,836 --> 00:09:11,139
- No, Chairman.
- No, Chairman.

82
00:09:11,139 --> 00:09:12,561
That isn't true at all.

83
00:09:12,561 --> 00:09:14,682
You're still going strong, sir.

84
00:09:14,682 --> 00:09:17,786
Kang Jae Gyeong, Kang Jae Seong,

85
00:09:18,438 --> 00:09:23,739
bring me results
that'll win the board in a month.

86
00:09:23,739 --> 00:09:26,527
I'll make my call then.

87
00:09:30,505 --> 00:09:32,066
That's all.

88
00:09:34,636 --> 00:09:36,705
Chairman.

89
00:09:36,705 --> 00:09:39,305
Father.

90
00:09:42,477 --> 00:09:44,345
So what now?

91
00:09:44,345 --> 00:09:47,969
Should we kneel in the lobby and beg?

92
00:09:47,969 --> 00:09:50,456
He could at least drop a hint,

93
00:09:50,456 --> 00:09:53,454
but he wants us to crawl to the twins.

94
00:09:54,294 --> 00:09:58,059
He handed him Trading for being the eldest,

95
00:09:58,059 --> 00:10:00,395
and every deal he touches goes bust.

96
00:10:00,395 --> 00:10:03,238
Aside from handing posts
to his buddies and in-laws,

97
00:10:03,238 --> 00:10:04,255
what has he done?

98
00:10:04,255 --> 00:10:05,800
What about Kang Jae Gyeong?

99
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,306
She grows Chemicals a bit
and walks around with her nose up,

100
00:10:08,306 --> 00:10:10,638
treating her staff like dirt,
and that's nothing new.

101
00:10:10,638 --> 00:10:12,196
My vote's for President Kang Jae Gyeong.

102
00:10:12,196 --> 00:10:16,239
You saw President Kang Jae Seong,
still half asleep.

103
00:10:16,239 --> 00:10:18,979
Father.

104
00:10:19,805 --> 00:10:23,584
Not a word yesterday and now a succession?

105
00:10:23,584 --> 00:10:25,358
Stop blindsiding your kids.

106
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:27,317
Decide now.

107
00:10:27,317 --> 00:10:28,698
I'm ready, Father.

108
00:10:28,698 --> 00:10:30,191
You think I'm not?

109
00:10:30,191 --> 00:10:32,969
When it comes to confidence, that's me.

110
00:10:32,969 --> 00:10:35,263
By natural order, the chair's mine.

111
00:10:35,263 --> 00:10:37,632
Doesn't Choiseong run on firstborn succession?

112
00:10:37,632 --> 00:10:39,273
You never once treated me

113
00:10:39,273 --> 00:10:40,701
differently for being a girl.

114
00:10:40,701 --> 00:10:42,358
You signed me up for boxing over ballet,

115
00:10:42,358 --> 00:10:45,039
and I remember how you lit up
when I floored those boys.

116
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:48,497
Choiseong runs on merit.

117
00:10:48,497 --> 00:10:51,546
What, want me to tell him
one of those boys was you?

118
00:10:51,546 --> 00:10:54,772
Where are your manners with your big brother?

119
00:10:54,772 --> 00:10:58,018
Fifty seconds older
and you play the big brother.

120
00:10:59,705 --> 00:11:02,056
The stage is set,

121
00:11:02,056 --> 00:11:04,790
so fight it out for a month.

122
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:06,628
You're both so sure,

123
00:11:06,628 --> 00:11:11,832
we'll find out who's dirty and who's lacking.

124
00:11:27,349 --> 00:11:29,817
Get every Trading exec in here.

125
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:34,622
Redo every division's performance report.

126
00:11:34,622 --> 00:11:37,294
Where are we on Yuncheon Port
and the coal terminal?

127
00:11:37,294 --> 00:11:40,027
The environmental groups are pushing back hard.

128
00:11:40,027 --> 00:11:41,963
And the locals aren't happy either.

129
00:11:41,963 --> 00:11:45,213
So we just sit on our hands?

130
00:11:45,213 --> 00:11:47,647
Tell them we'll meet their terms,

131
00:11:47,647 --> 00:11:49,804
just sweet-talk them.

132
00:11:49,804 --> 00:11:51,793
Look at Director Song,

133
00:11:51,793 --> 00:11:54,373
solar plant up and running,

134
00:11:54,373 --> 00:11:57,111
hydrogen plant moving along smoothly.

135
00:11:57,111 --> 00:11:58,805
Sir, about that,

136
00:11:58,805 --> 00:12:00,914
Opung City isn't being cooperative.

137
00:12:00,914 --> 00:12:03,918
We may need to scale it back.

138
00:12:03,918 --> 00:12:06,988
We should be inflating it, not shrinking it.

139
00:12:06,988 --> 00:12:09,139
Scale back?

140
00:12:09,139 --> 00:12:11,692
The Singapore mall site,

141
00:12:11,692 --> 00:12:14,671
the fire recovery costs are no joke, sir.

142
00:12:14,671 --> 00:12:17,451
Are you all praying I lose the chair?

143
00:12:17,451 --> 00:12:19,830
Is this whole room working for Kang Jae Gyeong?

144
00:12:19,830 --> 00:12:22,303
Bury the losses out of sight,

145
00:12:22,303 --> 00:12:25,411
and pump the rest up as big as it'll go.

146
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:28,271
That's how we beat Choiseong Chemicals!
Are we clear?

147
00:12:28,271 --> 00:12:30,144
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

148
00:12:30,144 --> 00:12:32,980
Of Choiseong Chemicals' recent wins,

149
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:36,550
what's the biggest one in your eyes?

150
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,320
The crown jewel for Chemicals

151
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:40,454
is Choiseong Energy, hands down.

152
00:12:40,454 --> 00:12:42,869
Our lithium-ion battery locked down

153
00:12:42,869 --> 00:12:44,892
the small-cell market,

154
00:12:44,892 --> 00:12:47,995
and we're pushing hard on solid-state

155
00:12:47,995 --> 00:12:51,040
to solve the overheating issue at its root.

156
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:54,201
Choiseong Chemical
is the main driver of Choiseong.

157
00:12:54,201 --> 00:12:56,600
I'm confident we'll be the driving force

158
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:59,540
that lifts Korea's economy
in the global battery market.

159
00:13:02,710 --> 00:13:04,259
Owning the narrative is key.

160
00:13:04,259 --> 00:13:07,048
- Secretary Yeo, push the article.
- Pushing it now.

161
00:13:07,048 --> 00:13:09,016
The press play kicks it off.

162
00:13:09,016 --> 00:13:11,252
I'll send the release and start the pitches.

163
00:13:11,252 --> 00:13:12,405
[Future of Choiseong, Leader Kang Jae Gyeong]

164
00:13:12,405 --> 00:13:14,989
- Push it out now, please.
- Got it.

165
00:13:14,989 --> 00:13:17,191
[Please find the attached
press release for your review]

166
00:13:17,191 --> 00:13:19,314
[Future of Choiseong, Leader Kang Jae Gyeong]
["Core is Battery R&amp;D"]

167
00:13:20,906 --> 00:13:21,962
[President Kang Jae Gyeong is incredible]

168
00:13:21,962 --> 00:13:23,130
[Choiseong plus batteries equals number one]

169
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:24,932
[Chemicals stock is going up! Let's ride!]

170
00:13:24,932 --> 00:13:26,133
[Recommend, Like, Insightful, Angry]

171
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:27,767
[Recommend, Support, Sad, Want a follow-up]

172
00:13:47,855 --> 00:13:51,493
[Certificate of Merit]
[Certificate of Distinguished Service Medal]

173
00:13:51,493 --> 00:13:54,490
Have you really made up your mind, Chairman?

174
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:57,999
Every business group now
has a chairman in their 40s or 50s.

175
00:13:57,999 --> 00:13:59,589
And besides,

176
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:02,503
I've already said I'm stepping down.

177
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:09,438
The twins will come charging,

178
00:14:09,438 --> 00:14:13,120
and others will line up behind them.

179
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:16,518
You're going to split them into camps?

180
00:14:16,518 --> 00:14:19,461
You want infighting inside the group?

181
00:14:21,106 --> 00:14:23,223
The bigger the chaos,

182
00:14:24,879 --> 00:14:27,895
the clearer the wheat from the chaff.

183
00:14:29,712 --> 00:14:33,367
Not one of them sits right with you,

184
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:36,603
so you'll seat whoever rallies the most support

185
00:14:37,238 --> 00:14:39,845
and rule from behind the scenes.

186
00:14:42,577 --> 00:14:45,124
Lee Sang Jae,

187
00:14:45,124 --> 00:14:48,405
I should have had you as my own.

188
00:14:48,405 --> 00:14:49,750
Right?

189
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:50,990
[Approval]

190
00:14:55,162 --> 00:14:56,758
Where are you off to, sir?

191
00:14:56,758 --> 00:14:59,384
I figured I'd clock out on time for once.

192
00:15:00,083 --> 00:15:01,795
Clocking out.

193
00:15:07,805 --> 00:15:10,437
The Chairman is leaving.

194
00:15:33,804 --> 00:15:36,598
Where are we on what I ordered?

195
00:16:24,746 --> 00:16:27,088
It's seafood stew, dear.

196
00:16:33,239 --> 00:16:34,755
This is good.

197
00:16:36,324 --> 00:16:38,759
The oysters were so fresh,

198
00:16:38,759 --> 00:16:41,788
they practically begged me to take them home.

199
00:16:41,788 --> 00:16:43,632
The seasons turn and your energy dips.

200
00:16:43,632 --> 00:16:45,882
Honey.

201
00:16:45,882 --> 00:16:47,401
Save it.

202
00:16:48,469 --> 00:16:49,739
End of verse one,

203
00:16:49,739 --> 00:16:51,472
no verse two.

204
00:16:51,472 --> 00:16:54,606
You two, no business talk at the table

205
00:16:54,606 --> 00:16:56,410
so your father can eat in peace.

206
00:16:56,410 --> 00:17:00,204
The battery project is getting great buzz.

207
00:17:00,204 --> 00:17:02,216
The solid-state news even pushed

208
00:17:02,216 --> 00:17:05,486
the group's stock up. Did you see?

209
00:17:05,486 --> 00:17:07,855
The stock rose thanks to Choiseong Trading

210
00:17:07,855 --> 00:17:11,892
making news with the Yuncheon SOC project.

211
00:17:11,892 --> 00:17:14,672
The article about our 30,000-ton
coal terminal berth

212
00:17:14,672 --> 00:17:16,230
at Yuncheon Port.

213
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:19,800
Locals and environmental groups
are protesting it.

214
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:22,403
Expanding the port creates jobs.

215
00:17:22,403 --> 00:17:23,861
Their protests won't get them anywhere.

216
00:17:23,861 --> 00:17:26,306
Got any leverage to shut them down?

217
00:17:30,106 --> 00:17:33,885
Since when does a company
sweat citizens and activists?

218
00:17:33,885 --> 00:17:35,883
That's a job for the bureaucrats,

219
00:17:35,883 --> 00:17:39,646
you crunch the numbers
and call it profit or loss.

220
00:17:39,646 --> 00:17:41,488
Honestly,

221
00:17:41,488 --> 00:17:44,758
how are you fit to be chair?

222
00:17:44,758 --> 00:17:46,259
The chairmanship?

223
00:17:46,259 --> 00:17:49,065
You're handing it down already?

224
00:17:49,065 --> 00:17:50,325
What do you mean, already?

225
00:17:50,325 --> 00:17:53,868
Father has worked his whole life,

226
00:17:53,868 --> 00:17:56,203
he should get some rest.

227
00:17:57,172 --> 00:18:00,040
He could travel with you,

228
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,344
wouldn't that be nice?

229
00:18:01,344 --> 00:18:04,257
Not a word and out of nowhere?

230
00:18:04,257 --> 00:18:07,181
Is something broken in you?

231
00:18:07,181 --> 00:18:09,917
Did you catch something you haven't told me?

232
00:18:09,917 --> 00:18:11,818
Enough nonsense.

233
00:18:12,454 --> 00:18:15,469
I'll soak after dinner. My body feels heavy.

234
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:20,761
Chairman, I'm here.

235
00:18:20,761 --> 00:18:23,132
What brings you here at this hour?

236
00:18:23,132 --> 00:18:27,569
The Chairman said he'd hit the track,
so I came to pick him up.

237
00:18:27,569 --> 00:18:30,104
He wants to test the new battery.

238
00:18:30,104 --> 00:18:32,506
You didn't say anything,

239
00:18:32,506 --> 00:18:35,770
you were just heading for a soak.

240
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:37,978
There's a thrill to night driving.

241
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:41,783
Your timing's perfect.

242
00:19:08,909 --> 00:19:10,691
Why can't I ever reach you?

243
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:12,280
What? I'm busy.

244
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:15,415
Looks like your father's stepping down.

245
00:19:16,617 --> 00:19:20,188
Get on your sister and brother's good side

246
00:19:20,188 --> 00:19:22,489
and let's bring you back to Korea.

247
00:19:22,489 --> 00:19:25,839
Once succession is set
and they see you want no share,

248
00:19:25,839 --> 00:19:28,607
would they really keep you in America forever?

249
00:19:28,607 --> 00:19:30,931
What, do I come and go on your command?

250
00:19:30,931 --> 00:19:32,866
Isn't it morning in New York?

251
00:19:32,866 --> 00:19:34,466
Why is it so loud?

252
00:19:34,466 --> 00:19:35,936
Were you out clubbing all night?

253
00:19:35,936 --> 00:19:37,067
I'm hanging up.

254
00:19:37,067 --> 00:19:38,639
Bang Geul.

255
00:19:38,639 --> 00:19:40,240
Kang Bang Geul.

256
00:19:45,605 --> 00:19:47,781
The director's glass is empty.

257
00:19:47,781 --> 00:19:49,338
Yes.

258
00:19:49,338 --> 00:19:51,118
I'll be right back in.

259
00:19:51,118 --> 00:19:54,475
Which team are you on again?

260
00:19:54,475 --> 00:19:57,993
Materials Team 2 intern, Casey Kang.

261
00:19:57,993 --> 00:20:00,306
Okay.

262
00:20:00,306 --> 00:20:01,572
Let's go.

263
00:20:01,572 --> 00:20:03,864
Let's go.

264
00:20:03,864 --> 00:20:05,799
Offshore slush funds?

265
00:20:05,799 --> 00:20:08,608
We've confirmed 300 billion
under Kang Jae Seong,

266
00:20:08,608 --> 00:20:10,671
and 350 billion under Kang Jae Gyeong

267
00:20:10,671 --> 00:20:11,939
[Special Audit Report: Corporate Slush Funds]
in hidden funds.

268
00:20:11,939 --> 00:20:15,410
You couldn't have dug this up
in just a few days.

269
00:20:16,143 --> 00:20:18,764
Did you wait for the announcement?

270
00:20:18,764 --> 00:20:20,025
To throw me under the bus?

271
00:20:20,025 --> 00:20:21,116
I'm sorry, sir.

272
00:20:21,116 --> 00:20:23,283
I had to verify it twice.

273
00:20:25,144 --> 00:20:27,387
So it's airtight.

274
00:20:30,424 --> 00:20:32,957
Your head's full, why not run a lap first?

275
00:20:32,957 --> 00:20:34,726
That's why I brought you here.

276
00:20:34,726 --> 00:20:37,326
A slap on the wrist and a pat on the back?

277
00:20:37,326 --> 00:20:39,833
Walking's the right move now.

278
00:20:49,405 --> 00:20:51,678
The Chairman just left.

279
00:21:23,210 --> 00:21:25,135
You scared me.

280
00:21:26,424 --> 00:21:27,571
Did you follow me?

281
00:21:27,571 --> 00:21:30,418
Director Lee called Father out here,
it's obvious.

282
00:21:30,418 --> 00:21:32,953
He's slipping him something on the sly.

283
00:21:33,820 --> 00:21:36,591
And it's about us.

284
00:21:36,591 --> 00:21:38,491
You've got dirt too?

285
00:21:39,728 --> 00:21:42,562
As dirty as the one tailing him?

286
00:21:43,197 --> 00:21:44,851
This is mine.

287
00:21:44,851 --> 00:21:46,611
Hand it over while I'm asking nicely.

288
00:21:46,611 --> 00:21:47,791
Hands off.

289
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:49,970
There you go again.

290
00:21:53,074 --> 00:21:55,835
Battery swap done?

291
00:21:55,835 --> 00:21:58,411
Manager Jang handled it.

292
00:22:00,538 --> 00:22:03,116
I'll take a lap.

293
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:06,013
No matter how far I walk,

294
00:22:06,705 --> 00:22:09,363
my head won't cool down.

295
00:22:09,363 --> 00:22:11,291
Give it back.

296
00:22:11,893 --> 00:22:13,981
I swear, you.

297
00:22:15,662 --> 00:22:16,672
- What?
- What was that?

298
00:22:16,672 --> 00:22:18,632
Father didn't leave?

299
00:22:18,632 --> 00:22:20,163
- Floor it.
- What?

300
00:22:20,163 --> 00:22:23,169
We're caught red-handed.
We're done, just floor it!

301
00:22:36,383 --> 00:22:38,151
What happened here?

302
00:22:45,339 --> 00:22:47,027
Unreal.

303
00:22:56,006 --> 00:22:57,604
Manager Jang, cover for me.

304
00:22:57,604 --> 00:22:59,172
[Manager Jang Moon Ho]
Spin a story.

305
00:22:59,172 --> 00:23:01,174
I was never there.

306
00:23:05,658 --> 00:23:07,114
What happened here?

307
00:23:07,114 --> 00:23:09,129
Well,

308
00:23:09,129 --> 00:23:12,954
the motor sounded off,
so I sent it to the shop.

309
00:23:12,954 --> 00:23:14,521
You said the swap was done.

310
00:23:14,521 --> 00:23:16,123
The Chairman's safety is on the line,

311
00:23:16,123 --> 00:23:18,048
so I wanted to be sure.

312
00:23:18,048 --> 00:23:20,595
Should I bring another car?

313
00:23:20,595 --> 00:23:22,068
Don't bother.

314
00:23:23,297 --> 00:23:26,733
Driving on a night like this always ends bad.

315
00:23:35,162 --> 00:23:37,072
K League leaders Choiseong FC

316
00:23:37,072 --> 00:23:40,480
[Hwang Jun Hyeon]
announced today they signed Hwang Jun Hyeon.

317
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:43,972
After three years with FC Sunyang,
Hwang Jun Hyeon

318
00:23:43,972 --> 00:23:48,106
started 31 matches with 13 goals and 9 assists,

319
00:23:48,106 --> 00:23:50,590
winning K League 2 MVP.

320
00:23:50,590 --> 00:23:53,906
["I Will Make Choiseong FC Champions."]
After a fierce bidding war,

321
00:23:53,906 --> 00:23:57,102
his move to Choiseong FC is now official.

322
00:23:57,102 --> 00:24:00,467
- With huge appeal and outstanding...
- That's my grandson.

323
00:24:01,605 --> 00:24:04,438
Congratulations.

324
00:24:04,438 --> 00:24:06,206
There he is.

325
00:24:07,339 --> 00:24:08,908
Grandma!

326
00:24:11,072 --> 00:24:13,048
That's not him.

327
00:24:13,048 --> 00:24:15,482
My grandson Jun Hyeon

328
00:24:15,482 --> 00:24:18,218
is the soccer player Hwang Jun Hyeon.

329
00:24:19,152 --> 00:24:20,283
Look, see?

330
00:24:20,283 --> 00:24:22,189
Grandma.

331
00:24:22,189 --> 00:24:23,557
I'm your grandson, right?

332
00:24:23,557 --> 00:24:27,961
Choiseong FC, number 77,
striker Hwang Jun Hyeon!

333
00:24:27,961 --> 00:24:29,172
There you are!

334
00:24:29,172 --> 00:24:30,797
My grandson!

335
00:24:30,797 --> 00:24:32,532
The turf is unreal,

336
00:24:32,532 --> 00:24:34,099
and the jersey feels like silk.

337
00:24:34,099 --> 00:24:36,738
She's sharp the moment soccer comes up.

338
00:24:36,738 --> 00:24:39,906
Who'd ever guess Ok Sun has dementia?

339
00:24:39,906 --> 00:24:41,758
Just like you wished,

340
00:24:41,758 --> 00:24:43,798
I'll make it to the Premier League.

341
00:24:43,798 --> 00:24:46,079
The hard days are over.

342
00:24:52,139 --> 00:24:54,556
Why is there no sound?

343
00:24:54,556 --> 00:24:56,558
Can you see what it is?

344
00:24:56,558 --> 00:24:59,692
Father's gone, just drive to the track.

345
00:25:04,532 --> 00:25:06,246
Looks like overseas accounts.

346
00:25:06,246 --> 00:25:07,726
Where? Where exactly?

347
00:25:07,726 --> 00:25:09,146
- Quit it!
- Let me see!

348
00:25:09,146 --> 00:25:11,004
Just drive!

349
00:25:14,672 --> 00:25:17,477
I got your favorite chocolate cake too.

350
00:25:30,839 --> 00:25:32,926
What was that?

351
00:26:21,875 --> 00:26:24,311
Jun Hyeon.

352
00:26:24,311 --> 00:26:26,213
Answer me,

353
00:26:26,213 --> 00:26:28,239
say something,

354
00:26:28,239 --> 00:26:30,516
please, answer me.

355
00:26:39,639 --> 00:26:41,228
Male, twenties, traffic accident,

356
00:26:41,228 --> 00:26:42,729
unconscious, no BP reading.

357
00:26:42,729 --> 00:26:44,239
Family? Any family?

358
00:26:44,239 --> 00:26:46,359
He only has his grandmother,

359
00:26:46,359 --> 00:26:48,566
and she has dementia. What do we do?

360
00:26:48,566 --> 00:26:51,472
[Caregiver Auntie]
Suspected internal bleeding and leg fracture.

361
00:26:51,472 --> 00:26:53,273
Are you hurt?

362
00:26:53,273 --> 00:26:56,206
A cat darted out of nowhere,

363
00:26:56,206 --> 00:26:58,078
so I clipped the rail.

364
00:26:58,078 --> 00:27:01,648
Manager Jang, Father can never know.

365
00:27:01,648 --> 00:27:03,516
Are we clear?

366
00:27:04,851 --> 00:27:07,267
Police cams, road footage, dashcams,

367
00:27:07,267 --> 00:27:09,427
every witness, wipe it all.

368
00:27:09,427 --> 00:27:11,858
Clean it up before sunrise.

369
00:27:15,903 --> 00:27:18,064
The track's cameras are wiped,

370
00:27:18,064 --> 00:27:20,906
and the gate staff are silenced.

371
00:27:20,906 --> 00:27:22,202
Let's prep for emergency surgery.

372
00:27:22,202 --> 00:27:24,239
Right away.

373
00:27:24,239 --> 00:27:26,005
Hello?

374
00:27:27,239 --> 00:27:28,739
Yes.

375
00:27:28,739 --> 00:27:30,476
Understood.

376
00:27:34,547 --> 00:27:35,743
[Delete selected CCTV file?]
[Delete]

377
00:27:38,336 --> 00:27:39,352
[Delete]

378
00:27:39,352 --> 00:27:40,522
[Deletion complete]

379
00:27:40,522 --> 00:27:41,774
[Main OR]

380
00:28:17,139 --> 00:28:18,339
Good morning.

381
00:28:18,339 --> 00:28:20,039
Good morning.

382
00:28:20,039 --> 00:28:21,861
Good morning.

383
00:28:26,405 --> 00:28:28,368
The battery is fully swapped.

384
00:28:28,368 --> 00:28:31,604
One spin and you'll feel the difference.

385
00:28:52,659 --> 00:28:55,130
You patched the wrong spot.

386
00:28:55,130 --> 00:28:57,297
Did the kids drop by last night?

387
00:28:57,297 --> 00:28:58,605
No, sir.

388
00:28:58,605 --> 00:29:01,334
No, nothing like that.

389
00:29:24,088 --> 00:29:25,892
Please forgive me.

390
00:29:25,892 --> 00:29:29,164
Jae Seong said he swerved
for a cat and hit the rail,

391
00:29:29,164 --> 00:29:30,664
and nobody was hurt.

392
00:29:30,664 --> 00:29:33,866
He and Jae Gyeong ordered strict silence.

393
00:29:35,906 --> 00:29:38,801
The accident footage is wiped clean, right?

394
00:29:38,801 --> 00:29:40,422
When have I ever botched anything?

395
00:29:40,422 --> 00:29:43,461
Nothing botched,
so how did Father catch the slush funds?

396
00:29:43,461 --> 00:29:45,180
We don't know that.

397
00:29:45,180 --> 00:29:48,450
If Father knew, would he leave us alone?

398
00:29:48,450 --> 00:29:52,220
That document might not be a slush fund tip.

399
00:29:54,754 --> 00:29:56,489
It's coming to us anyway,

400
00:29:56,489 --> 00:29:58,391
so what's the harm in taking some early?

401
00:29:58,391 --> 00:30:00,739
It cuts the tax bill, that's all.

402
00:30:00,739 --> 00:30:02,696
At other groups, the chairman steps up

403
00:30:02,696 --> 00:30:04,176
and sets the slush funds up himself,

404
00:30:04,176 --> 00:30:06,900
handling the inheritance well in advance.

405
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:09,204
My friends are all chairmen already.

406
00:30:09,204 --> 00:30:12,174
The old man is just greedy.

407
00:30:13,323 --> 00:30:15,892
Is he planning to keep it all?

408
00:30:16,576 --> 00:30:17,883
What?

409
00:30:17,883 --> 00:30:21,139
He's been two steps
ahead of us this whole time,

410
00:30:21,139 --> 00:30:23,251
using that slush fund like a leash,

411
00:30:23,251 --> 00:30:25,652
squeezing more out of us.

412
00:30:25,652 --> 00:30:27,487
Is King Yeongjo his idol?

413
00:30:27,487 --> 00:30:28,805
Yanking us around

414
00:30:28,805 --> 00:30:32,225
just to torture us? He's losing it.

415
00:30:33,526 --> 00:30:36,765
We'll never measure up in Dad's eyes.

416
00:30:36,765 --> 00:30:39,772
Even with the chairman's seat,

417
00:30:39,772 --> 00:30:43,074
we'd still be tiptoeing around him,

418
00:30:43,074 --> 00:30:48,040
bowing for whatever crumbs he drops.

419
00:30:49,044 --> 00:30:52,614
What a miserable life.

420
00:30:52,614 --> 00:30:54,013
That kid.

421
00:30:55,172 --> 00:30:56,949
Did he survive?

422
00:31:52,603 --> 00:31:55,443
You're awake, Mr. Hwang.

423
00:31:55,443 --> 00:31:57,276
How are you feeling?

424
00:31:59,039 --> 00:32:01,283
The surgery went well,

425
00:32:01,283 --> 00:32:03,903
and daily life won't be a problem.

426
00:32:03,903 --> 00:32:06,731
But with multiple ligament tears,

427
00:32:06,731 --> 00:32:08,006
including the PCL,

428
00:32:08,006 --> 00:32:09,823
and the leg fracture,

429
00:32:09,823 --> 00:32:12,823
rehab won't be easy.

430
00:32:12,823 --> 00:32:14,564
I'm sorry to say...

431
00:32:14,564 --> 00:32:16,572
soccer

432
00:32:16,572 --> 00:32:18,531
is off the table.

433
00:32:22,404 --> 00:32:23,852
What?

434
00:32:27,006 --> 00:32:29,275
What are you saying?

435
00:32:30,263 --> 00:32:32,078
You said the surgery went well.

436
00:32:32,078 --> 00:32:34,239
We did everything we could.

437
00:32:34,239 --> 00:32:35,915
I'm sorry.

438
00:32:38,939 --> 00:32:41,621
No, no, Doctor.

439
00:32:42,268 --> 00:32:44,757
You want to know what trying everything means?

440
00:32:46,239 --> 00:32:48,228
[Strict Bed Rest]
For over fifteen years, no days off,

441
00:32:48,228 --> 00:32:51,097
I trained at five every morning.

442
00:32:55,533 --> 00:32:58,204
She forgets her own name,

443
00:33:03,672 --> 00:33:05,939
but never that her grandson plays soccer.

444
00:33:05,939 --> 00:33:08,614
For my grandma's sake,

445
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:13,786
I never even said it was hard.

446
00:33:16,322 --> 00:33:17,757
I'll play again.

447
00:33:17,757 --> 00:33:20,092
I have to, no matter what.

448
00:33:21,373 --> 00:33:23,329
So please,

449
00:33:24,139 --> 00:33:27,900
just fix my leg.

450
00:33:30,872 --> 00:33:33,606
I'm begging you.

451
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:45,368
With the slush fund confirmed,

452
00:33:45,368 --> 00:33:47,989
[Internal Special Audit Report: Choiseong Group]
handing things over is too soon.

453
00:33:47,989 --> 00:33:50,623
I'm sure this rattles you too.

454
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:54,126
You've seen how low they sink.

455
00:33:58,239 --> 00:33:59,932
Bury it.

456
00:34:01,534 --> 00:34:03,235
The slush fund.

457
00:34:04,005 --> 00:34:06,105
Every related document,

458
00:34:07,438 --> 00:34:09,672
destroy it for good.

459
00:34:09,672 --> 00:34:11,639
And keep the staff quiet.

460
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,413
This isn't a small amount, Sir.

461
00:34:13,413 --> 00:34:16,738
- If you keep cleaning up after them...
- Those brats.

462
00:34:16,738 --> 00:34:19,919
Looks like they hit my dashcam last night.

463
00:34:20,953 --> 00:34:24,523
And still you'll bury it?

464
00:34:26,139 --> 00:34:28,628
They've lived under my thumb their whole lives.

465
00:34:28,628 --> 00:34:32,901
Whoever takes over, I need to back them.

466
00:34:32,901 --> 00:34:36,404
I can't keep crushing them.

467
00:34:36,404 --> 00:34:38,039
Too scared of their father

468
00:34:38,039 --> 00:34:42,007
to do anything. I won't raise fools.

469
00:34:45,139 --> 00:34:47,079
Understood.

470
00:34:47,939 --> 00:34:49,282
Grab the files.

471
00:34:49,282 --> 00:34:50,401
[Special Audit Report: Corporate Slush Funds]

472
00:35:26,819 --> 00:35:29,655
This is the real estate
I set aside for my wife.

473
00:35:29,655 --> 00:35:33,659
Sell it and book it
as Trading and Chemicals revenue.

474
00:35:33,659 --> 00:35:36,647
Before anyone catches wind and points fingers.

475
00:35:36,647 --> 00:35:38,467
Yes.

476
00:35:38,467 --> 00:35:41,206
Then the succession announcement
proceeds as planned.

477
00:35:41,206 --> 00:35:43,169
I'll prepare for it.

478
00:35:46,505 --> 00:35:48,906
Money doesn't change much.

479
00:35:48,906 --> 00:35:51,644
Every parent's guilty in the end.

480
00:35:54,839 --> 00:35:57,450
You can't keep doing this.

481
00:35:58,405 --> 00:35:59,934
Don't pull on that.

482
00:35:59,934 --> 00:36:01,554
Settle down.

483
00:36:01,554 --> 00:36:04,073
[I can make a comeback. Please, just trust me]

484
00:36:05,658 --> 00:36:07,034
[Coach, Choiseong FC]

485
00:36:09,805 --> 00:36:14,233
The number's unavailable. After the tone...

486
00:36:21,741 --> 00:36:23,667
[Caregiver Auntie]

487
00:36:28,948 --> 00:36:30,589
[An overdue interest payment
of 2 million won has been detected]

488
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:47,039
Grab the bar.

489
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:48,670
Hold the bar.

490
00:36:48,670 --> 00:36:50,400
You okay?

491
00:37:21,699 --> 00:37:23,802
Sir, I'm here.

492
00:37:27,602 --> 00:37:29,414
It's been a while.

493
00:37:29,414 --> 00:37:32,400
Whenever something big came up,
we'd start the morning here.

494
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:35,014
Son or grandson takes it over,

495
00:37:35,014 --> 00:37:36,885
the broth tastes the same.

496
00:37:36,885 --> 00:37:39,519
So does the kkakdugi.

497
00:37:39,519 --> 00:37:44,159
Took me this long
to see how big a deal that is.

498
00:37:44,159 --> 00:37:46,741
Don't end up with regrets like mine.

499
00:37:46,741 --> 00:37:48,363
Put the work into raising your kids.

500
00:37:48,363 --> 00:37:50,772
I was planning to.

501
00:37:50,772 --> 00:37:53,501
When you step down, I'm out too.

502
00:37:53,501 --> 00:37:56,302
So that's why you pushed me to stay?

503
00:37:56,302 --> 00:37:57,503
Missing the paycheck already?

504
00:37:57,503 --> 00:37:59,338
Just figured it out?

505
00:38:07,538 --> 00:38:09,949
Who you'll hand it to,

506
00:38:11,106 --> 00:38:13,152
have you decided?

507
00:38:14,656 --> 00:38:16,606
I have to.

508
00:38:18,794 --> 00:38:20,528
Whoever...

509
00:38:20,528 --> 00:38:23,752
protects Choiseong the most.

510
00:38:50,692 --> 00:38:52,478
325 yeo...

511
00:38:55,561 --> 00:38:58,117
[325 yeo 20]

512
00:39:00,166 --> 00:39:01,180
[325 yeo 20]

513
00:39:02,501 --> 00:39:03,501
[325 yeo 20]

514
00:39:10,406 --> 00:39:12,645
I saw the plate clear as day.

515
00:39:12,645 --> 00:39:15,881
325 yeo 20.

516
00:39:15,881 --> 00:39:18,651
325 yeo 20.

517
00:39:20,639 --> 00:39:22,106
The rest is a blank.

518
00:39:22,106 --> 00:39:24,156
That's only a hundred combos left.

519
00:39:24,156 --> 00:39:26,172
A search will find it.

520
00:39:26,172 --> 00:39:28,239
There was a strange emblem
on the back bumper too.

521
00:39:28,239 --> 00:39:29,998
What about proof?

522
00:39:29,998 --> 00:39:32,798
A photo or video of the plate?

523
00:39:32,798 --> 00:39:35,772
The street cams would've caught it.

524
00:39:35,772 --> 00:39:37,770
That spot's a blind spot,

525
00:39:37,770 --> 00:39:40,640
and the backup recorder was down that day.

526
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,942
There's nothing on file.

527
00:39:42,942 --> 00:39:45,647
I can't open a case based on memory alone.

528
00:39:53,359 --> 00:39:55,954
No evidence found from the victim.

529
00:39:59,039 --> 00:40:00,393
I'm done here.

530
00:40:00,393 --> 00:40:02,330
What about Choiseong FC?

531
00:40:02,330 --> 00:40:03,986
How did it go?

532
00:40:05,981 --> 00:40:07,533
A penalty fee?

533
00:40:07,533 --> 00:40:10,069
I gave back every won of the signing bonus!

534
00:40:10,069 --> 00:40:11,672
[General Manager Han Jae Kwon]

535
00:40:11,672 --> 00:40:14,339
There's the transfer fee we paid for you.

536
00:40:14,339 --> 00:40:16,572
Choiseong FC took a big hit too.

537
00:40:16,572 --> 00:40:20,112
I hate to say it, but the contract's off.

538
00:40:20,958 --> 00:40:23,082
Sir.

539
00:40:23,082 --> 00:40:24,772
I can rehab through this.

540
00:40:24,772 --> 00:40:26,959
Watch me. I'll prove I can come back.

541
00:40:26,959 --> 00:40:28,921
So please...

542
00:40:30,425 --> 00:40:33,043
Just give me one shot.

543
00:40:33,043 --> 00:40:35,256
Morale's at rock bottom.

544
00:40:35,256 --> 00:40:38,864
Fact is, you set the team back.

545
00:40:38,864 --> 00:40:40,617
But a billion won in penalties?

546
00:40:40,617 --> 00:40:43,039
That's just cruel.

547
00:40:43,039 --> 00:40:44,737
The call came from upstairs.

548
00:40:44,737 --> 00:40:46,905
Our hands are tied.

549
00:40:47,976 --> 00:40:50,979
He's buried in debt he can't dig out of.

550
00:40:50,979 --> 00:40:53,145
That'll keep him in line.

551
00:40:53,145 --> 00:40:58,476
[Seeking Witnesses to Traffic Accident]

552
00:41:22,942 --> 00:41:25,572
[Caregiver Auntie]

553
00:41:25,572 --> 00:41:26,872
Hello?

554
00:41:26,872 --> 00:41:28,468
Why haven't you picked up?

555
00:41:28,468 --> 00:41:30,349
I've been worried sick.

556
00:41:31,219 --> 00:41:33,306
Auntie.

557
00:41:33,306 --> 00:41:35,003
You've been through hell.

558
00:41:35,003 --> 00:41:37,189
It's all going to be okay.

559
00:41:39,125 --> 00:41:40,962
Nothing's okay.

560
00:41:40,962 --> 00:41:43,363
They say there's no evidence.

561
00:41:43,363 --> 00:41:44,797
What do you mean, no evidence?

562
00:41:44,797 --> 00:41:47,032
Did you not get what I sent?

563
00:41:48,306 --> 00:41:50,302
So Grandma has something to watch,

564
00:41:50,302 --> 00:41:52,838
I record every video call.

565
00:41:58,110 --> 00:42:00,006
[325 yeo 2058]

566
00:42:00,006 --> 00:42:03,048
325 yeo 2058.

567
00:42:04,617 --> 00:42:05,651
[License Plate Lookup]

568
00:42:05,651 --> 00:42:06,651
[Full Vehicle History]

569
00:42:07,639 --> 00:42:09,524
[325 yeo 2058]

570
00:42:09,524 --> 00:42:10,956
[Search Third-Party Vehicle]

571
00:42:10,956 --> 00:42:11,791
[325 yeo 2058]

572
00:42:11,791 --> 00:42:13,315
[Maserati MC 20 Cielo]

573
00:42:18,164 --> 00:42:20,174
[Only Ten of These Electric
Supercars Worldwide]

574
00:42:21,634 --> 00:42:27,039
[Speed Junkie!
Chairman Kang Lands a Supercar]

575
00:42:30,342 --> 00:42:32,906
[F1 fan Chairman Kang unwinds
with stacks of F1 magazines]

576
00:42:33,639 --> 00:42:35,881
Happiness, my foot.

577
00:42:48,227 --> 00:42:49,500
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

578
00:42:57,470 --> 00:42:58,506
[To: Chairman Kang, From: F1 Magazine]

579
00:42:58,506 --> 00:43:00,400
This month's issue already arrived.

580
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:01,639
It's a special edition.

581
00:43:01,639 --> 00:43:04,276
He ordered it. Rush delivery.

582
00:43:05,448 --> 00:43:07,505
Send it up to the Chairman's office.

583
00:43:07,505 --> 00:43:10,473
[Special Edition Inside]

584
00:43:30,672 --> 00:43:33,652
Want to see what happens next? Call me.

585
00:43:33,652 --> 00:43:36,441
Owner of 325 yeo 2058.

586
00:43:46,906 --> 00:43:50,322
The Chairman wants you upstairs.

587
00:44:05,822 --> 00:44:08,239
Hwang Jun Hyeon.

588
00:44:08,239 --> 00:44:10,876
That was a bold little stunt.

589
00:44:11,542 --> 00:44:14,880
I don't take being wronged lying down.

590
00:44:16,081 --> 00:44:18,083
Wronged, huh.

591
00:44:20,553 --> 00:44:24,556
Let's see if you can keep
a straight face after this.

592
00:44:40,763 --> 00:44:42,306
Please forgive me.

593
00:44:42,306 --> 00:44:45,377
Jae Seong said he swerved
for a cat and hit the rail.

594
00:44:45,377 --> 00:44:48,847
He and Jae Gyeong ordered strict silence.

595
00:44:48,847 --> 00:44:52,651
Because of you, my soccer career is over.

596
00:44:52,651 --> 00:44:56,488
I was thrilled to join Choiseong FC!

597
00:44:57,122 --> 00:44:59,458
Cutting my contract, slapping me with fines.

598
00:44:59,458 --> 00:45:02,188
You thought I'd run scared?

599
00:45:02,188 --> 00:45:03,972
Faking evidence, buying off cops,

600
00:45:03,972 --> 00:45:06,698
you really thought that would bury the truth?

601
00:45:16,991 --> 00:45:19,111
So how much do you want?

602
00:45:22,206 --> 00:45:25,083
A decent person starts
with an apology, don't they?

603
00:45:28,739 --> 00:45:31,423
For me, an apology is money.

604
00:45:32,057 --> 00:45:36,364
Nothing says sorry deeper than a check.

605
00:45:36,364 --> 00:45:38,931
You'll be better off with it.

606
00:45:38,931 --> 00:45:40,866
What about my life?

607
00:45:41,491 --> 00:45:44,436
You ruin a life and think cash fixes it?

608
00:45:46,464 --> 00:45:49,041
Hwang Jun Hyeon's career file

609
00:45:49,651 --> 00:45:52,906
and the Choiseong FC contract, bring them.

610
00:45:52,906 --> 00:45:55,214
Right away, Sir.

611
00:45:55,214 --> 00:45:56,682
[From Rookie of the Year to MVP:
The Rise of Hwang Jun Hyeon]

612
00:45:56,682 --> 00:45:58,200
[Professional Soccer Player Contract]

613
00:45:59,472 --> 00:46:01,954
Signed a month ago for 500 million.

614
00:46:01,954 --> 00:46:05,172
On the national team, knocked down by injury,

615
00:46:05,172 --> 00:46:07,798
looks like you've had it rough.

616
00:46:07,798 --> 00:46:11,129
What do you think you're worth?

617
00:46:12,075 --> 00:46:15,701
A soccer career usually lasts

618
00:46:15,701 --> 00:46:17,839
till the mid-thirties.

619
00:46:17,839 --> 00:46:19,996
Another decade for you?

620
00:46:19,996 --> 00:46:21,707
Where are you going with this?

621
00:46:21,707 --> 00:46:25,106
Even if luck spared you at Choiseong FC

622
00:46:25,106 --> 00:46:27,449
and you played injury-free,

623
00:46:27,449 --> 00:46:30,182
your top salary tops out at 5 billion won.

624
00:46:32,168 --> 00:46:34,172
That sum,

625
00:46:34,172 --> 00:46:35,821
I'll pay it.

626
00:46:36,608 --> 00:46:38,877
And the penalty fees? Gone.

627
00:46:40,104 --> 00:46:44,099
That's enough to start over, whatever you do.

628
00:46:44,099 --> 00:46:45,730
In exchange,

629
00:46:46,665 --> 00:46:48,867
hand over the video.

630
00:46:52,639 --> 00:46:53,842
And if I refuse?

631
00:46:53,842 --> 00:46:57,543
Stop running on emotion. Think.

632
00:46:57,543 --> 00:46:59,154
Even if you walk into a police station,

633
00:46:59,154 --> 00:47:02,247
push the video at them, and press charges,

634
00:47:02,247 --> 00:47:05,939
I take a little heat, hit the news a few times,

635
00:47:05,939 --> 00:47:09,221
step down briefly, and it's done.

636
00:47:10,118 --> 00:47:12,624
You'd trade a windfall for that?

637
00:47:14,493 --> 00:47:17,958
The world always bends your way. Fun for you?

638
00:47:17,958 --> 00:47:20,699
Who are you to write off my future?

639
00:47:20,699 --> 00:47:22,906
A few sheets of paper with my history,

640
00:47:22,906 --> 00:47:26,238
is my life so pathetic
you can price it in minutes?

641
00:47:26,238 --> 00:47:27,779
Whether I'm the next Messi or Son Heung Min,

642
00:47:27,779 --> 00:47:30,275
who made you the judge?

643
00:47:30,275 --> 00:47:32,010
Because you can't.

644
00:47:32,805 --> 00:47:36,815
A kid who hears "no hope"
and runs in chasing a payout?

645
00:47:37,686 --> 00:47:39,432
What does he become?

646
00:47:40,252 --> 00:47:41,954
What if I sue?

647
00:47:41,954 --> 00:47:43,918
Fight to the end, prove the hit-and-run,

648
00:47:43,918 --> 00:47:46,591
bring Choiseong down. What then?

649
00:47:49,839 --> 00:47:53,132
You think my Choiseong falls that easy?

650
00:47:53,132 --> 00:47:55,233
To someone like you?

651
00:48:00,839 --> 00:48:03,942
Soccer was my whole life too.

652
00:48:05,377 --> 00:48:08,758
More than Choiseong ever was to you.

653
00:48:08,758 --> 00:48:11,819
Me reaching the Premier League,
that's my grandma's dream.

654
00:48:11,819 --> 00:48:14,031
All the pain I put her through,

655
00:48:14,031 --> 00:48:18,001
every drop of sweat I left on that field,
can you price that?

656
00:48:19,373 --> 00:48:20,892
You'll get it.

657
00:48:21,627 --> 00:48:24,129
Whatever amount you want.

658
00:48:29,971 --> 00:48:31,248
[Blank Check]

659
00:48:32,704 --> 00:48:35,505
[Issuer: Kang Yong Ho]
Want ten billion? Write ten billion.

660
00:48:35,505 --> 00:48:37,042
I'm curious too.

661
00:48:37,042 --> 00:48:39,314
For that grand life of yours,

662
00:48:39,314 --> 00:48:42,013
what number you'll land on.

663
00:48:51,306 --> 00:48:55,202
Sir, the Presidents are here.

664
00:48:55,202 --> 00:48:58,206
If you decide to bury this here,

665
00:48:58,206 --> 00:48:59,998
come back and see me.

666
00:49:01,139 --> 00:49:03,335
No more negotiating.

667
00:49:14,330 --> 00:49:15,371
Because you can't.

668
00:49:15,371 --> 00:49:19,605
A kid who hears "no hope"
and runs in chasing a payout?

669
00:49:19,605 --> 00:49:21,320
What does he become?

670
00:49:21,320 --> 00:49:22,331
You'll get it.

671
00:49:22,331 --> 00:49:24,723
Whatever amount you want.

672
00:49:27,438 --> 00:49:30,231
I'm sorry.

673
00:49:30,231 --> 00:49:32,297
- Who's this punk?
- Doors closing.

674
00:49:43,172 --> 00:49:45,277
5 billion won...

675
00:49:45,894 --> 00:49:49,441
I can put Grandma in a better place.

676
00:49:49,441 --> 00:49:52,808
That clears every debt we have.

677
00:49:52,808 --> 00:49:56,120
I can do anything with that.

678
00:49:56,120 --> 00:49:58,123
With that...

679
00:50:02,068 --> 00:50:03,598
I'm curious too.

680
00:50:03,598 --> 00:50:05,843
For that grand life of yours,

681
00:50:05,843 --> 00:50:08,533
what number you'll land on.

682
00:50:09,668 --> 00:50:12,257
[Blank Check]

683
00:50:20,245 --> 00:50:21,765
[Grandma]

684
00:50:30,306 --> 00:50:32,223
Jun Hyeon.

685
00:50:33,862 --> 00:50:35,311
Grandma.

686
00:50:35,311 --> 00:50:37,999
She's done with the gown.

687
00:50:37,999 --> 00:50:40,598
She wants out so she can hit the stadium.

688
00:50:40,598 --> 00:50:42,000
Ok Sun, come on.

689
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:43,011
Look.

690
00:50:43,011 --> 00:50:45,139
I can eat just fine on my own.

691
00:50:56,515 --> 00:50:58,306
Ok Sun.

692
00:50:58,306 --> 00:51:00,474
What team does Jun Hyeon play for?

693
00:51:00,474 --> 00:51:01,520
Choiseong FC.

694
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:03,438
That's right!

695
00:51:03,438 --> 00:51:04,615
Nicely done.

696
00:51:04,615 --> 00:51:07,893
So what's his number?

697
00:51:07,893 --> 00:51:12,172
Lucky seven, seven. Number 77.

698
00:51:12,172 --> 00:51:14,255
And his position?

699
00:51:14,255 --> 00:51:16,901
Striker!

700
00:51:18,303 --> 00:51:20,615
Your grandma's a genius.

701
00:51:20,615 --> 00:51:24,042
Auntie, I'll call you back later.

702
00:51:35,439 --> 00:51:37,722
Go get them, my boy!

703
00:51:41,072 --> 00:51:43,661
Grandma, I'm sorry.

704
00:51:45,219 --> 00:51:47,966
They say soccer's over for me.

705
00:51:51,605 --> 00:51:54,572
I broke our promise.

706
00:51:55,805 --> 00:51:58,643
What do I do now?

707
00:52:03,705 --> 00:52:05,339
Attention, please.

708
00:52:05,339 --> 00:52:08,653
The Chairman's board meeting starts shortly,

709
00:52:08,653 --> 00:52:10,489
so all listed executives,

710
00:52:10,489 --> 00:52:14,195
please gather in the third-floor boardroom.

711
00:52:14,195 --> 00:52:15,694
Attention, please.

712
00:52:15,694 --> 00:52:18,964
The Chairman's board meeting starts shortly,

713
00:52:18,964 --> 00:52:20,832
so all listed executives,

714
00:52:20,832 --> 00:52:24,736
please gather in the third-floor boardroom.

715
00:52:46,458 --> 00:52:48,061
I'm sorry, Dad.

716
00:52:48,061 --> 00:52:51,001
Jae Seong was driving.

717
00:52:51,001 --> 00:52:54,088
All I did was clean it up.

718
00:52:54,088 --> 00:52:56,668
Jae Gyeong's the one who whispered to run.

719
00:52:56,668 --> 00:52:59,373
If she hadn't lost it over the dashcam,

720
00:52:59,373 --> 00:53:01,940
there'd be no accident. I swear.

721
00:53:04,273 --> 00:53:05,343
One.

722
00:53:05,343 --> 00:53:07,605
Letting Strategic Planning
catch the slush fund.

723
00:53:07,605 --> 00:53:10,182
Sloppy work on your part.

724
00:53:10,182 --> 00:53:11,538
Two.

725
00:53:11,538 --> 00:53:13,075
Digging into me without fear,

726
00:53:13,075 --> 00:53:15,963
then wrecking my prized car.

727
00:53:15,963 --> 00:53:17,583
Three.

728
00:53:17,583 --> 00:53:19,438
Botching the cleanup

729
00:53:19,438 --> 00:53:22,561
and smearing my name!

730
00:53:22,561 --> 00:53:26,349
Neither of you can run Choiseong.

731
00:53:26,349 --> 00:53:28,700
Forget about the Chairman's chair.

732
00:53:28,700 --> 00:53:31,039
I'll announce it at the board.

733
00:53:31,039 --> 00:53:32,980
You two,

734
00:53:33,808 --> 00:53:36,644
get ready to step down.

735
00:53:39,839 --> 00:53:41,149
Dad!

736
00:53:41,149 --> 00:53:42,814
Dad!

737
00:53:46,659 --> 00:53:48,739
Close the door already.

738
00:53:48,739 --> 00:53:50,048
Dad!

739
00:53:51,426 --> 00:53:52,911
Damn it.

740
00:53:53,639 --> 00:53:54,779
The stairs!

741
00:53:54,779 --> 00:53:56,728
- Stairs!
- Stairs.

742
00:53:57,696 --> 00:53:58,763
It's him!

743
00:53:58,763 --> 00:54:00,565
The young guy from the Chairman's office!

744
00:54:00,565 --> 00:54:01,600
That Hwang guy...

745
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:03,520
How did he find us here?

746
00:54:03,520 --> 00:54:05,203
You said you wiped it all!

747
00:54:05,203 --> 00:54:06,872
How could you mess up the job like this?

748
00:54:06,872 --> 00:54:09,373
Fact is, you were driving when it happened!

749
00:54:09,373 --> 00:54:13,039
If I get fired as President, you're dead.

750
00:54:13,039 --> 00:54:14,782
Like I'm going down alone?

751
00:54:14,782 --> 00:54:15,983
Hey, hold up.

752
00:54:15,983 --> 00:54:17,006
- Hold up.
- Come on.

753
00:54:17,006 --> 00:54:18,872
- Hold up.
- Like I'll stop for you!

754
00:54:18,872 --> 00:54:20,658
- Seriously.
- Hurry.

755
00:54:36,171 --> 00:54:37,918
- Stop!
- Stop!

756
00:54:43,678 --> 00:54:45,956
Dad!

757
00:54:50,815 --> 00:54:51,872
Sir!

758
00:54:51,872 --> 00:54:53,618
Dad!

759
00:55:35,651 --> 00:55:36,670
What?

760
00:55:36,670 --> 00:55:39,139
Why's it so loud?

761
00:55:39,139 --> 00:55:41,705
Sang Jae...

762
00:55:41,705 --> 00:55:43,801
Where did he go?

763
00:55:45,507 --> 00:55:47,208
My leg...

764
00:55:48,006 --> 00:55:50,241
My leg is moving.

765
00:55:52,438 --> 00:55:54,090
What?

766
00:55:54,090 --> 00:55:55,780
Am I dreaming?

767
00:55:58,006 --> 00:55:59,178
What?

768
00:55:59,178 --> 00:56:01,556
A hospital?

769
00:56:01,556 --> 00:56:03,357
What is this?

770
00:56:11,239 --> 00:56:13,231
Straight to resuscitation.

771
00:56:35,605 --> 00:56:37,088
Mr. Hwang.

772
00:56:38,006 --> 00:56:39,527
Are you awake?

773
00:56:39,527 --> 00:56:41,438
Hey, you.

774
00:56:41,438 --> 00:56:43,298
Who am I to you right now?

775
00:56:43,298 --> 00:56:45,289
You look like Hwang Jun Hyeon.

776
00:56:45,289 --> 00:56:46,305
That's right, isn't it?

777
00:56:46,305 --> 00:56:48,066
Of all people,

778
00:56:48,066 --> 00:56:50,168
why am I that kid?

779
00:56:50,168 --> 00:56:52,839
You've been out a day. You need rest.

780
00:56:52,839 --> 00:56:54,605
Hold on.

781
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:57,309
How many fingers?

782
00:56:57,309 --> 00:56:59,605
Forget that.

783
00:56:59,605 --> 00:57:01,012
Where...

784
00:57:01,012 --> 00:57:03,285
Where is the real me?

785
00:57:03,285 --> 00:57:04,544
Well...

786
00:57:04,544 --> 00:57:07,006
Set up another brain CT for Mr. Hwang.

787
00:57:07,006 --> 00:57:08,072
Got it.

788
00:57:08,072 --> 00:57:10,822
No, that's not what I mean...

789
00:57:13,241 --> 00:57:14,244
This place...

790
00:57:14,244 --> 00:57:15,444
Which hospital is this?

791
00:57:15,444 --> 00:57:17,295
This is Hangang University Hospital.

792
00:57:17,295 --> 00:57:18,972
First we need a scan of your head...

793
00:57:18,972 --> 00:57:21,119
Seriously!

794
00:57:21,119 --> 00:57:22,124
Mr. Hwang.

795
00:57:22,124 --> 00:57:23,868
Why is this working?

796
00:57:23,868 --> 00:57:25,607
Mr. Hwang.

797
00:57:28,939 --> 00:57:31,342
Looks like a temporary shock.

798
00:57:32,582 --> 00:57:35,753
Then why isn't he waking up?

799
00:57:38,705 --> 00:57:39,939
He's just sleeping.

800
00:57:39,939 --> 00:57:42,050
The MRI came back clean,

801
00:57:42,050 --> 00:57:43,892
so there's nothing to worry about.

802
00:57:43,892 --> 00:57:46,157
He's always been so healthy.

803
00:57:46,157 --> 00:57:49,898
Just to be safe, run more tests.

804
00:57:49,898 --> 00:57:52,731
That sudden succession call,

805
00:57:52,731 --> 00:57:54,336
it bothers me.

806
00:57:54,336 --> 00:57:56,604
This is so annoying.

807
00:57:57,435 --> 00:57:59,214
Why should a stay-at-home wife

808
00:57:59,214 --> 00:58:01,967
care who runs the company?

809
00:58:01,967 --> 00:58:03,106
Jae Gyeong,

810
00:58:03,106 --> 00:58:05,756
I'm just worried about him.

811
00:58:05,756 --> 00:58:07,329
Right,

812
00:58:07,329 --> 00:58:09,720
just worry, then.

813
00:58:09,720 --> 00:58:12,383
You've always stuck to that.

814
00:58:14,052 --> 00:58:16,020
Please don't worry.

815
00:58:16,020 --> 00:58:18,390
He'll wake up soon.

816
00:58:18,390 --> 00:58:19,646
Of course.

817
00:58:19,646 --> 00:58:21,225
He has to.

818
00:58:32,910 --> 00:58:34,976
Before the accident,

819
00:58:34,976 --> 00:58:37,543
did something happen?

820
00:58:37,543 --> 00:58:39,377
You came running,

821
00:58:39,377 --> 00:58:41,373
trying to stop him,

822
00:58:41,373 --> 00:58:43,657
shouting "Stop."

823
00:58:43,657 --> 00:58:45,966
Stop what?

824
00:58:45,966 --> 00:58:46,971
No, we didn't.

825
00:58:46,971 --> 00:58:48,620
- Stop!
- Stop!

826
00:58:48,620 --> 00:58:50,488
When did we do that?

827
00:58:56,605 --> 00:58:58,396
That guy who fell with him?

828
00:58:58,396 --> 00:58:59,664
No clue.

829
00:58:59,664 --> 00:59:02,357
But it wasn't a fall.

830
00:59:02,357 --> 00:59:03,805
Didn't he shove him?

831
00:59:03,805 --> 00:59:05,306
Watch your mouth.

832
00:59:05,306 --> 00:59:07,378
The intranet's blowing up,

833
00:59:07,378 --> 00:59:10,111
saying he headbutted the guy and went down.

834
00:59:10,111 --> 00:59:14,048
There's history with that man for sure.

835
00:59:14,705 --> 00:59:16,851
What's gotten into him?

836
00:59:16,851 --> 00:59:20,638
Out of nowhere, succession and now this.

837
00:59:20,638 --> 00:59:22,805
Never a scandal in his life,

838
00:59:22,805 --> 00:59:25,623
so maybe it's really time.

839
00:59:28,538 --> 00:59:30,438
Ears everywhere.

840
00:59:30,438 --> 00:59:34,599
The company's in crisis, so zip it.

841
00:59:34,599 --> 00:59:35,731
Right.

842
00:59:35,731 --> 00:59:37,539
How's the Chairman?

843
00:59:37,539 --> 00:59:39,440
Any sign he'll wake up?

844
00:59:47,078 --> 00:59:48,569
[BREAKING:
Choiseong's Kang linked to hit-and-run]

845
00:59:51,049 --> 00:59:52,150
[BREAKING:
Kang's car in hit-and-run; assault tip filed]

846
00:59:52,150 --> 00:59:54,206
- What?
- What is this?

847
00:59:54,206 --> 00:59:55,753
We have breaking news.

848
00:59:55,753 --> 00:59:58,405
The recent hit-and-run by the Choiseong Circuit

849
00:59:58,405 --> 01:00:01,092
has been tied to a vehicle owned

850
01:00:01,092 --> 01:00:04,162
by Chairman Kang Yong Ho, shocking the public.

851
01:00:04,162 --> 01:00:07,398
An anonymous tip claims he verbally

852
01:00:07,398 --> 01:00:10,039
and physically abused the victim,

853
01:00:10,039 --> 01:00:12,237
with major fallout expected.

854
01:00:12,237 --> 01:00:14,772
The victim is now being treated

855
01:00:14,772 --> 01:00:16,805
at an undisclosed Seoul hospital.

856
01:00:16,805 --> 01:00:19,344
Some witnesses say Chairman Kang

857
01:00:19,344 --> 01:00:22,447
charged at the victim first.

858
01:00:22,447 --> 01:00:25,817
His exact condition and what really happened

859
01:00:25,817 --> 01:00:27,373
remain unconfirmed.

860
01:00:27,373 --> 01:00:29,557
I don't take being wronged lying down.

861
01:00:29,557 --> 01:00:31,519
Wronged, huh.

862
01:00:32,372 --> 01:00:34,206
Faking evidence, buying off cops,

863
01:00:34,206 --> 01:00:36,894
you really thought that would bury the truth?

864
01:00:40,869 --> 01:00:42,737
Secrets are leaking.

865
01:00:42,737 --> 01:00:45,136
Check if the victim's awake,

866
01:00:45,136 --> 01:00:46,304
and secure him first.

867
01:00:46,304 --> 01:00:47,939
Yes, on it.

868
01:00:53,805 --> 01:00:56,514
The Chairman, a hit-and-run?

869
01:00:56,514 --> 01:00:58,983
Do you two know anything?

870
01:00:59,984 --> 01:01:02,763
This caught us off guard too.

871
01:01:02,763 --> 01:01:05,723
Before the board meeting,

872
01:01:05,723 --> 01:01:08,583
he pulled us aside and gave us a hint.

873
01:01:08,583 --> 01:01:10,899
All I did was clean it up.

874
01:01:10,899 --> 01:01:13,247
I had no idea about the hit-and-run.

875
01:01:17,772 --> 01:01:19,422
That's right.

876
01:01:19,422 --> 01:01:22,043
He'd been silencing the victim all along.

877
01:01:22,043 --> 01:01:24,874
If she hadn't lost it over the dashcam,

878
01:01:24,874 --> 01:01:26,043
there'd be no accident. I swear.

879
01:01:26,043 --> 01:01:27,306
Afraid it would all come out,

880
01:01:27,306 --> 01:01:29,583
he rushed the succession.

881
01:01:29,583 --> 01:01:33,421
So the Chairman actually

882
01:01:33,421 --> 01:01:36,320
admitted the hit-and-run to you both?

883
01:01:39,639 --> 01:01:41,239
Dad!

884
01:01:41,239 --> 01:01:44,795
Please tell us the truth.

885
01:01:45,872 --> 01:01:47,098
Yes,

886
01:01:47,098 --> 01:01:51,202
he caused the accident.

887
01:01:58,705 --> 01:02:01,851
Like hell he did!

888
01:02:01,851 --> 01:02:04,648
You damn bastards!

889
01:02:20,472 --> 01:02:22,006
Who are you?

890
01:02:22,006 --> 01:02:24,005
Move aside.

891
01:02:24,005 --> 01:02:26,270
I'm getting my body back.

892
01:02:49,805 --> 01:02:51,228
Honey.

893
01:02:52,106 --> 01:02:53,798
Honey.

894
01:03:34,139 --> 01:03:35,634
Know who I am?

895
01:03:35,634 --> 01:03:38,176
Was that punk trying to headbutt Father?

896
01:03:38,176 --> 01:03:38,954
Dad.

897
01:03:38,954 --> 01:03:41,454
Prepare for the worst.

898
01:03:41,454 --> 01:03:44,353
[Stop the cover-up, pay up!]
Your career's done, so take the payout.

899
01:03:44,353 --> 01:03:46,114
You're getting whatever you want.

900
01:03:46,114 --> 01:03:47,874
The hit-and-run's been buried.

901
01:03:47,874 --> 01:03:49,574
You'd better see this through for me.

902
01:03:49,574 --> 01:03:52,104
I'm Hwang Jun Hyeon, intern at Choiseong.

903
01:03:52,104 --> 01:03:54,684
Looking forward to working with you.

904
01:03:54,684 --> 01:03:56,627
So this is Materials Team 2.

905
01:03:56,627 --> 01:03:59,097
Does he report to you?
Who are you, the Chairman?

906
01:03:59,097 --> 01:04:00,331
Me!

907
01:04:00,331 --> 01:04:01,471
We call her Yes Kang.

908
01:04:01,471 --> 01:04:02,191
I'll handle it.

909
01:04:02,191 --> 01:04:03,591
She's our team's gem.

910
01:04:03,591 --> 01:04:05,811
If you tell anyone
I'm the Chairman's daughter, you're dead.

911
01:04:05,811 --> 01:04:08,570
About Casey...

912
01:04:08,570 --> 01:04:10,608
The Chairman's awake?

913
01:04:10,608 --> 01:04:12,447
[Copying files]
Father said that? That we did it?

914
01:04:12,447 --> 01:04:13,739
Got proof?

915
01:04:13,739 --> 01:04:14,791
Here to steal something?

916
01:04:14,791 --> 01:04:15,772
Call the cops!

917
01:04:15,772 --> 01:04:17,771
Don't let him out of here.

918
01:04:17,771 --> 01:04:21,418
[Choiseong Emergency Press Conference]
The real culprit who ran me down is...
